%U A397120 4947046255852,28071892396801,159293178835888,903904968715531,5129184481081714,29105421152813995,165157935643383226
%N A397120 Size of Type A Megastars of star triples in the Spectre aperiodic monotile tiling.
%C A397120 The chiral aperiodic Spectre monotile tiling (discovered in 2023) forms hierarchical, fractal macro-structures called clusters of star triples (three Spectre tiles head-on) of five different families, megastars of two types, and palindromes of megastars. This sequence represents the total number of star triples in successive generations of Type A megastars. The fractal growth is governed by the limiting constant 5.674473356937... = 1 + 2*sqrt(6) * cos((1/3) * arccos(sqrt(6)/4)), which is the largest root of the cubic equation x^3 - 3*x^2 - 15*x - 1 = 0.
%H A397120 Boris K. Horvat, <a href="/A397120/b397120.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..100</a>
%H A397120 Boris K. Horvat, <a href="https://zenodo.org/records/18421797">Anatomy of the Spectre Tiling</a>, Zenodo, 2026.
%H A397120 David Smith, J. S. Myers, C. S. Kaplan, and C. Goodman-Strauss, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2305.17743">A chiral aperiodic monotile</a>, arXiv:2305.17743 [math.CO], 2023-2024.
%H A397120 <a href="/index/Rec#order_03">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (3,15,1).
%F A397120 a(n) = 3*a(n-1) + 15*a(n-2) + a(n-3) (for n>3, where a(1)=1, a(2)=4, a(3)=25).
%F A397120 a(n) = a(n-1) + 3*A397121(n-1) (for n>1, with a(1)=1, A397121(0)=0).
%F A397120 a(n) = 1 + 3*A397115(n-1) (for n>0, with A397115(0)=0).
%F A397120 a(n) = c_1*r_1^n + c_2*r_2^n + c_3*r_3^n, where r_1, r_2, r_3 are the roots of x^3 - 3*x^2 - 15*x - 1 = 0.
%F A397120 G.f.: (1 - x)*(1 + 2*x)/(1 - 3*x - 15*x^2 - x^3). - _Stefano Spezia_, Jun 27 2026
%e A397120 For n = 2, the Type A Megastar has a(2) = 4 star triples. It is formed by the previous generation's megastar a(1) = 1 and is inflated/extended by three Type C Megastars of size MC(1) = 1, giving 1 + 3*1 = 4 star triples.
%e A397120 For n = 3, the Type A Megastar has a(3) = 25 star triples. It is formed by the previous generation's megastar a(1) = 4 and is inflated/extended by three Type C Megastars of size MC(2) = 7, giving 4 + 3*7 = 25 star triples.
%t A397120 LinearRecurrence[{3, 15, 1}, {1, 4, 25}, 24] (* _Amiram Eldar_, Jun 27 2026 *)
%Y A397120 Cf. A397115 (Family A), A397116 (Family C), A397117 (Family B), A397118 (Family D), A397119 (Family E), A397121 (Megastar C), A397122 (Palindrome A), A397123 (Sequence A).
